The paper presents a novel graph-based neural network model for relation extraction, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the model involves deep learning and neural networks, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of walks and iterative updates also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
